This topic explains how to install Ops Manager on Microsoft Azure manually.

To install Ops Manager on Azure manually, do the following:

1. Deploy Ops Manager. See [Deploying Ops Manager on Azure](../azure/deploy-manual.html).

1. Configure BOSH Director. See [Configuring BOSH Director on Azure](../azure/config-manual.html).

## <a id="next"></a> Next Steps

After completing the procedures above, configure a runtime.

For information about installing and configuring a runtime, see the following:

* [Configuring PAS](https://docs.pivotal.io/application-service/2-7/operating/configure-pas.html).
* [Installing TKGI on Azure](https://docs.pivotal.io/tkgi/installing-cli.html).
